        "story_id": "hf:google/gemma-4-26b-a4b-it",
        "summary": "Hugging Face | Launch Blog | Documentation License: Apache 2.0 | Authors: Google DeepMind Gemma is a family of open models built by Google DeepMind. Gemma 4 models are multimodal, handling text and image input (with audio supported on small models) and generating text output. This release includes open-weights models in both pre-trained and instruction-tuned variants. Gemma 4 features a context window of up to 256K tokens and maintains multilingual support in over 140 languages. Featuring both Dense and Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) architectures, Gemma 4 is well-suited for tasks like text generation, coding, and reasoning. The models are available in four distinct sizes: **E2B**, **E4B**, **26B A4B**, and **31B**. Their diverse sizes make them deployable in environments ranging from high-end...",
